 oh no said the countess taking her hand i could go all around the world with you and never be dull you are one of those delightful women in whose company sweet either to be silent or to chat now please fret over your son you expect never to be parted 
 madame karenina stood quite still holding herself very erect and her eyes were smiling 
 anna arkadyevna the countess said in explanation to her son has a little son eight years old i believe and she has never been parted from him before and she keeps fretting over leaving him 
 yes the countess and i have been talking all the time i of my son and she of hers said madame karenina and again a smile lighted up her face a caressing smile intended for him 
 i am afraid that you must have been dreadfully bored he said promptly catching the ball of coquetry she had flung him but apparently she did not care to pursue the conversation in that strain and she turned to the old countess 
 thank you so much the time has passed so quickly countess 
 my love answered the countess let me kiss your pretty face i speak plainly at my age and i tell you simply that lost my heart to you 
 stereotyped as the phrase was madame karenina obviously believed it and was delighted by it she flushed bent down slightly and put her cheek to the lips drew herself up again and with the same smile fluttering between her lips and her eyes she gave her hand to vronsky he pressed the little hand she gave him and was delighted as though at something special by the energetic squeeze with which she freely and vigorously shook his hand she went out with the rapid step which bore her rather fully developed figure with such strange lightness 
 very charming said the countess 
