 when anna entered the tiny drawing room she found dolly sitting there with a plump little boy already resembling his father she was listening to a lesson in french reading as the boy read he kept twisting and trying to tear off a button that was nearly off his jacket his mother had several times taken his hand from it but the plump little hand went back to the button again his mother pulled the button off and put it in her pocket 
 keep your hands still grisha she said and she took up her work a coverlet she had long been making she always set to work on it at depressed moments and now she knitted at it nervously twitching her fingers and counting the stitches though she had sent word the day before to her husband that it was nothing to her whether his sister came or not she had made everything ready for her arrival and was expecting her with agitation 
 dolly was crushed by her sorrow utterly swallowed up by it still she did not forget that anna her was the wife of one of the most important personages in peterburg and was a peterburg grande dame and thanks to this circumstance she did not carry out her threat to her husband that is to say she had not forgotten that her was coming and after all anna is in no wise to blame thought dolly i know nothing save the very best about her and i have seen nothing but kindness and affection from her toward myself it was true that as far as she could recall her impressions at peterburg at the she did not like their household itself there was something artificial about the whole arrangement of their family life but why should i not receive her if only she take it into her head to console me thought dolly all consolations and exhortations and christian forgiveness i have thought all this over a thousand times and all no use 
 all these days dolly had been alone with her children she did not want to talk of her sorrow but with that sorrow in her heart she could not talk of outside matters 
 she knew that in one way or another she would tell anna everything and she was alternately glad at the thought of speaking freely and angry at the necessity of speaking of her humiliation with her his sister and of hearing her phrases of exhortation and consolation 
 she had been on the lookout for her glancing at her watch every minute and as often happens let slip that precise minute when her visitor arrived so that she did not hear the bell 
 catching the sound of skirts and of light steps at the door she looked round and her careworn face unconsciously expressed not gladness but wonder she got up and embraced her 
 what here already she said as she kissed her 
 dolly how glad i am to see you 
 i am glad too said dolly faintly smiling and trying by the expression of face to find out whether she knew most likely she knows she thought noticing the sympathy in face well come along take you to your room she went on trying to defer as long as possible the time of explanation 
 is this grisha heavens how grown said anna and kissing him never taking her eyes off dolly she stood still and flushed no please let us stay here 
 she took off her shawl and her hat and catching it in a lock of her black hair which was a mass of curls she tossed her head and shook her hair down 
 you are radiant with health and happiness said dolly almost with envy 
 i yes said anna merciful heavens tania the same age as my seriozha she added addressing the little girl as she ran in she took her in her arms and kissed her delightful child delightful show me them all 
 she mentioned them not only remembering the names but the years months characters illnesses of all the children and dolly could not but appreciate that 
 very well we will go to them she said a pity asleep 
 after seeing the children they sat down alone now in the drawing room to coffee anna took the tray and then pushed it away from her 
 dolly she said he has told me 
 dolly looked coldly at anna she was waiting now for hypocritically sympathetic phrases but anna said nothing of the sort 
 dolly darling she said i want to intercede for him nor to try to comfort you impossible but my dearest simply sorry sorry from my heart for you 
